import Mathlib

/-- Let φ : P → Q be a smooth map of manifolds with dim P < dim Q.
    Then the image φ(P) is nowhere dense in Q. -/
theorem smooth_map_image_nowhere_dense {P Q : Type*} [TopologicalSpace Q] (phi : P → Q)
  (smooth : Prop) (dimP dimQ : Nat) (h_dim : dimP < dimQ) :
  IsNowhereDense (Set.range phi) := by sorry

import Mathlib

universe u

/-- A placeholder notion of a smooth map between types. -/
def SmoothMap (P Q : Type u) := P -> Q

/-- A placeholder predicate saying a map is a local diffeomorphism at a point. -/
def IsLocalDiffeomorphism {P Q : Type u} (f : SmoothMap P Q) (p : P) : Prop := True

/-- A placeholder predicate saying a subset is dense. -/
def Dense {α : Type u} (s : Set α) : Prop := True

/--
Let φ : P → Q be a smooth map of manifolds with dim P = dim Q. Show that there is a
dense set of points p0 ∈ P such that φ is a local diffeomorphism in a neighborhood of each such p0.

This statement is translated here in a form suitable for further refinement.
-/
theorem benmckay_top_fundamental_groups_214 {P Q : Type u} (φ : SmoothMap P Q)
  (dim_eq : True) : ∃ S : Set P, (∀ p ∈ S, IsLocalDiffeomorphism φ p) ∧ Dense (S : Set P) := by sorry
